1
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:03,840
Kajorn, what are you doing?

2
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,600
You're finally mine.

3
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,640
I'm here to talk to you about Kajorn.

4
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,880
This is the very first time we've met.

5
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,480
Why should I share stories
about my lover with you?

6
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:13,600
So you found me here

7
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:16,200
because you can't handle
my crazy family in Phuket, huh?

8
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,000
You're from Phuket, Uncle?

9
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,440
I am from Phuket as well.

10
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,720
If I could turn back time…

11
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:25,600
What would you want to change, Uncle Ree?

12
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,240
I wouldn't want to change a thing.

13
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:29,320
Are you talking about the fortune?

14
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,480
To be right by my fortune.

15
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:45,240
I was chased down by that Wild Bull,
yet you're still laughing?

16
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,280
What is your heart made of?

17
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:50,960
Well, what did you expect me to do?

18
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:54,440
Neither of you would tell me
what the fight was even about.

19
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,080
He only said

20
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:58,560
you took his money.

21
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:01,640
I couldn't just blindly intervene.

22
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:06,120
Let's find something to eat,

23
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:07,840
so we can return to Phuket.

24
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,120
Alright.

25
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:12,760
Tri.

26
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,800
Sasi.

27
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:34,400
Your life is always so eventful, Tri.

28
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:37,560
Even in Phuket, you still manage
to stay extraordinary.

29
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:40,760
Extraordinary?

30
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,360
Is that a polite way of saying unlucky?

31
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:06,720
And what about you, Sasi?
How have you been?

32
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,200
I…

33
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:17,959
I'm engaged now.

34
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,600
Congratulations.

35
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,320
Also,

36
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:42,960
please pass along my best wishes
to that lucky man as well.

37
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,400
Thank you.

38
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:14,200
Your friend's niece is quite lovely.

39
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:17,280
You should've invited her to join us.

40
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:21,320
Better not. I have far too many secrets.

41
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:25,360
Besides, Rajit is far too good

42
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:28,000
to be associated with a man like me.

43
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,240
In what way are you not a good man?

44
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,640
I misspoke.

45
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,240
I should've said

46
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,480
I'm just a man who's completely broke now.

47
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,200
That would be more accurate.

48
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:13,240
What took you so long?

49
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:17,480
And where did your friend go?

50
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:20,480
If you're that curious,
you should've just joined the table.

51
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:25,320
Well, I saw how eager you were
to talk to your friend.

52
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:27,880
I didn't want to be a third wheel.

53
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:34,080
Sasi already left, and so must we.

54
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:35,760
We still have a long way to Phuket.

55
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,240
Your friend is quite stunning.

56
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,520
She has such a soothing presence.

57
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,960
Is she just another friend,
like Ms. Srichan?

58
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,160
No, she isn't.

59
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,360
She's not a friend.

60
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,280
She's my ex-fiancée.

61
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,320
Let's go.

62
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:37,480
Huh?

63
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,520
What did you say?

64
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,400
You went to see Tri?

65
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,120
Yes.

66
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,320
We bumped into each other by accident.

67
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:48,040
Good heavens.

68
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,680
Why on earth did you meet him?

69
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,840
You already have a fiancé, Sasi.

70
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,400
Don't you forget that.

71
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,080
I haven't forgotten, Mother.

72
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,640
I haven't forgotten

73
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,640
that I had to break off my engagement
because he went bankrupt.

74
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,000
I haven't forgotten

75
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,400
that I had to rush into a new engagement

76
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,560
because our family
is running out of money, too.

77
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:11,640
Any pride or dignity I ever had

78
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,360
died long ago.

79
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:15,840
How could I forget that?

80
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:18,760
Are you talking back
to your own mother like this?

81
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:24,200
Please excuse me, Mother.

82
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,159
<i>Initially,</i>

83
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:41,600
<i>I intended to wait another year or two</i>

84
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:43,760
<i>before discussing the wedding.</i>

85
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:46,560
<i>However, my health is failing by the day.</i>

86
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:48,120
<i>I fear</i>

87
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:51,360
<i>I may pass away</i>
<i>before seeing Sasitorn settled down.</i>

88
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,200
<i>Do not hold it against me, son,</i>

89
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:57,640
<i>but I want the wedding</i>
<i>to happen as early as next month.</i>

90
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:03,840
One day, you'll understand
that I did all of this for you.

91
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,800
PHUKET

92
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:14,120
Your friend is quite stunning.

93
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,520
She has such a soothing presence.

94
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,440
She's not a friend.

95
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:21,960
She's my ex-fiancée.

96
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,400
Miss, you can't go up there.

97
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,200
You really can't.

98
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:34,920
Ms. Paetai strictly ordered
that you are not allowed upstairs.

99
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,760
As if I care. I've slapped her
with my own hands,

100
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,200
so why should I listen to you?

101
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,960
Miss, you can't go up there.

102
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,920
-You really can't.
-Noi.

103
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,840
Please go back to your chores.

104
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:47,000
I'll handle her myself.

105
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,320
-Let go of me.
-Yes, miss.

106
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:57,400
Uncle Ree isn't home.
He went to meet with the District Officer.

107
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:03,680
He vanishes for days, and the moment
I come over, he's missing.

108
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:06,760
Ms. Srichan.

109
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:11,560
Do you have a moment?

110
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,520
I'd like to talk about Ms. Sasitorn.

111
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,880
What? They actually ran into each other?

112
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:30,920
Uh, well, it was purely a coincidence.

113
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,560
Ms. Srichan.

114
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:42,360
Do you know why Ms. Sasitorn
and Uncle Ree broke up?

115
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,720
Looking for intel on your rival?

116
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,880
You must be jealous.

117
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,440
How can you say such a thing?

118
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:01,400
Why would I be jealous of my own uncle?

119
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,600
Right…

120
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:06,040
But I don't know much, honestly.

121
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:09,280
Tri never told me why they broke up.

122
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:13,960
If I had to guess, it was probably
because of money.

123
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,560
Well,

124
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,920
didn't Ms. Sasitorn
love Uncle Ree at all then?

125
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,640
How should I know?

126
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:25,680
But one thing's for sure, Tri loved her,

127
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:27,320
or he wouldn't have gotten engaged.

128
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,280
He probably loved her for a long time

129
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:33,040
since they grew up
next door to each other.

130
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:36,920
They only officially became a couple
after Tri returned from…

131
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,440
Uh…

132
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:42,720
From working in the province.

133
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:49,000
But now that Uncle Ree
inherited Grandpa's fortune,

134
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,440
he's a wealthy man.

135
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:54,200
Do you think

136
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,240
they might get back together?

137
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,320
And what about you?

138
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:08,040
Do you want them
to get back together or not?

139
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:18,440
Of course I'd want them
to get back together.

140
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:21,800
You hesitated.

141
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,440
I'd better get going.

142
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:27,960
Now that Sasitorn
seems to be making a comeback,

143
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:31,320
I need a new game plan
before their old flame reignites.

144
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,120
No more wasting time on you.

145
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,360
Oh.

146
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,160
Poor Uncle Ree.

147
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,840
PHUKET TOWN DISTRICT OFFICE

148
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,960
According to Colonel Nakamura,

149
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:53,800
this shipment includes rations,

150
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,800
fuel, weapons,

151
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,800
and military supplies.

152
00:12:58,640 --> 00:13:01,720
The Colonel fears
their escort is insufficient,

153
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,560
so he requested backup from me.

154
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,360
And what do you need me to do?

155
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,400
I have urgent business
to attend to in Bangkok

156
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:14,040
and must leave today.

157
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:17,520
Please assist Colonel Nakamura
on my behalf.

158
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,760
With pleasure.

159
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:21,720
Though,

160
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,920
handing over your work
for a long trip like this,

161
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:27,480
you're secretly visiting that fiancée
you mentioned, aren't you?

162
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:34,840
District Officer, Mr. Poj
is here to see you.

163
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:36,960
Mr. Poj.

164
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:39,720
What can I do for you?

165
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:44,000
How could I ever dare
to order a District Officer around?

166
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:47,160
I heard you'll be away for several days.

167
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,880
I might head back before you return.

168
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:52,040
So, I decided to drop by
with some souvenirs.

169
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,440
You shouldn't have, but thank you.

170
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,760
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

171
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:02,040
Thatri,

172
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:03,960
where are you going?

173
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,040
Thatri…

174
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,560
You bastard.

175
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,200
Even from Chiang Mai,

176
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:29,200
you still crept up here
to sleep with my wife?

177
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:34,400
You're sleeping with her, right?

178
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:37,120
Answer me! Spit it out!

179
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,800
How can I answer when you're choking me?

180
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,200
Stop it, Mr. Poj.

181
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,480
This is a government office.

182
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:44,400
If you attack me, I will report this.

183
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:49,000
Playing smart with me, are you?

184
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:52,480
Look, let's talk this out calmly.

185
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:56,280
I've never wrecked your home.
I'll even swear on my own life.

186
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,080
I don't buy it.

187
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:00,800
Think about it. If I actually did it,

188
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:02,640
Sri would be living with me by now,

189
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:06,040
or I'd be using her to drain your wealth.

190
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:08,360
But have you actually lost a single thing?

191
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,600
Think about it.

192
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:15,720
Fine. Then why are you
still chasing after her?

193
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,120
I've never chased her.

194
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:21,360
Are you suggesting
Srichan is the one chasing you?

195
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:23,440
What a self-centered jerk.

196
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:26,080
Can't you see
she's doing it just to spite you?

197
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:32,840
You two have been bickering
ever since you got married.

198
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:36,920
She loves to party,
while you do nothing but work.

199
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:41,080
Eventually, it led to a fight.
She knows how jealous you get,

200
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:43,600
so she's just using me
as a tool to hurt you.

201
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:48,360
To prove my sincerity,

202
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:51,800
how about I help you reconcile with Sri?

203
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:55,240
What's your plan then?

204
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:01,840
<i>To Srichan.</i>

205
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:06,480
<i>I'm in a state of distress,</i>
<i>and you are the only one</i>

206
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:09,120
<i>who can ease my mind.</i>

207
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:11,720
<i>For old times' sake,</i>

208
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:15,960
<i>come to Room 411</i>
<i>at Phuket Hotel tonight at 7:00 p.m.</i>

209
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:18,200
<i>Yours truly, Thatri.</i>

210
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:24,040
Desperate, aren't you? That's why
you're crawling right back to me.

211
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:29,120
Just you wait. I'll make you pay back

212
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:33,080
with interest and make it a night
you'll never forget.

213
00:16:36,520 --> 00:16:38,480
PHUKET HOTEL

214
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:42,280
Tri, I'm here.

215
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:01,920
Poj?

216
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,160
How did you get here?

217
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:05,839
I came here for you, of course.

218
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:14,040
Did you actually forge
Ree's letter to lure me out?

219
00:17:14,119 --> 00:17:16,400
But it worked, didn't it?

220
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,319
I know every single lie you've fed me.

221
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:21,640
How dare you

222
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,599
betray your own husband like this?

223
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,680
You bitch!

224
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:27,280
-Did you just call me that?
-Damn right!

225
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,800
And I'm going to do worse.

226
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:34,480
It's time you learned
how a proper wife should behave

227
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,720
after acting like a loose woman
for so long.

228
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,720
Poj.

229
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:42,680
What are you doing? Stop it!

230
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,040
Stay back!

231
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:01,360
Look at that bright smile.

232
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:04,760
I bet it's from meeting a special someone.

233
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:07,840
There's no one special.

234
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:11,160
I'm in a great mood
because I did a good deed.

235
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,800
Since when do you ever do anything good?

236
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,280
It wasn't just any good deed.

237
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:20,720
I played Cupid today.

238
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,120
-Cupid?
-Yes.

239
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:26,840
Are you going to treat
your wife like this again?

240
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:30,400
How could you do such a thing?

241
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:35,360
They are husband and wife.
It's no big deal.

242
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:38,960
A little back and forth,
and they'll make up.

243
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:42,360
You really have no understanding
of women, do you?

244
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:48,400
Look at you. You dirty old man!

245
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:52,320
No woman would ever love
or soften up to a man who abuses her.

246
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,200
Have you read too many trashy novels?

247
00:18:54,280 --> 00:18:55,480
Is it really that serious?

248
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:57,320
Come here you.

249
00:18:57,400 --> 00:19:00,600
-Do you yield yet?
-Yes, I do. I give up.

250
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:04,680
-But they're husband and wife.
-It doesn't matter.

251
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:07,320
You'd better prepare to visit Mr. Poj
at his sickbed tomorrow.

252
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:10,840
No way, you're exaggerating.

253
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:13,280
DISTRICT CHIEF'S RESIDENCE

254
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:16,600
I am terribly sorry, Mr. Poj.

255
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:25,000
You dirty old man.

256
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:28,200
You're saggy all over, yet you still
had the nerve to try to assault me?

257
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:32,520
Even though he was in the wrong,

258
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:35,680
he only did it because he wanted
to win you back.

259
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,520
He merely received
some misguided advice, that's all.

260
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,840
Please forgive him, Ms. Srichan.

261
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,160
I beg of you too, Sri.

262
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:48,960
Everything is my fault.

263
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:50,520
Even if you can't forgive me,

264
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:54,000
please consider the love
that Mr. Poj truly has for you.

265
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,560
But I don't love him.

266
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,960
I've said it many times,
I married him for his money.

267
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:03,960
I can't wait to divorce him,
so I can take the cash and find a new man.

268
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:05,760
Calm down, Sri.

269
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:08,560
I know you're just trying to provoke him.

270
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:11,280
Acting out of spite only serves your ego.

271
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:13,480
It never does any good for anyone.

272
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:15,360
Well, I don't care.

273
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,040
If it were up to me,

274
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:20,640
I'd divorce him and split
the assets right this second.

275
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,680
We can't do it right now.

276
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:27,960
But once we're back in Bangkok,
I'll give you a divorce.

277
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,640
Just be patient.

278
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:59,360
Once I'm back in Bangkok,
I'll get the divorce sorted out.

279
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:05,600
If you think she'll run to me
with your money like she claims,

280
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:07,120
you're mistaken.

281
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:10,440
She's only saying that to provoke you.

282
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,480
She'd never choose
a life of hardship with me.

283
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,320
I know…

284
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:19,680
But even without you,
Sri would leave anyway.

285
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,680
She despises me.

286
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:30,880
No matter what I do
or how much I give her,

287
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,320
it's never enough for her.

288
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:37,440
It was a mistake from the start.

289
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,640
I should've never loved her.

290
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:45,040
Love is never a mistake, Mr. Poj.

291
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:49,360
If Sri truly hated you,

292
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:51,760
she wouldn't have stayed for this long.

293
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:54,120
You know her better than anyone.

294
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:58,080
Yet she's leaving me now!

295
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:02,120
Calm down and gather yourself.

296
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:05,520
I wouldn't dare to lecture you,

297
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,480
but let me speak

298
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:10,880
as someone who has known
both you and Sri for years.

299
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:15,240
The issue between you two
stems from a lack of time

300
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:17,440
and excessive pride
more than anything else.

301
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,200
If you can find peace of mind,

302
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:23,160
I truly believe this can be resolved.

303
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:29,360
He thinks a divorce scares me?

304
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:31,720
All he ever does is work and make money,

305
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:33,360
constantly leaving me all by myself.

306
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:35,760
I am so utterly sick and tired of it.

307
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,480
But if you actually divorce Mr. Poj,

308
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:40,880
you'll suffer a massive loss.

309
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:46,800
I'm not stupid. I'll make sure
I walk away with a handsome settlement.

310
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:49,920
I didn't mean it in terms of money.

311
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:54,320
What else could an old man like him
possibly have left to give me?

312
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:58,000
It's love.

313
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:03,080
He might be older
and perhaps a bit boring in your eyes,

314
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:06,120
but no one will ever love you
as deeply as Mr. Poj does.

315
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:09,600
I believe you already know that.

316
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:27,120
Is this really for me?

317
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,560
Well, didn't you want it?

318
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:33,840
I haven't even said a single word.

319
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:37,760
I knew the moment I saw you looking at it.

320
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:39,200
We're husband and wife, after all.

321
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:42,560
In that case, could you put it on for me?

322
00:23:57,360 --> 00:24:00,520
It's going to look
absolutely stunning on your neck.

323
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:13,960
Thank you so much.

324
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:14,840
Sure.

325
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:23,760
That lady accused you
of selling your body to me?

326
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:27,800
She didn't dare say it to my face,
but she said it to my mother.

327
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:29,400
That makes no difference.

328
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,680
Just because she's some elite's wife,
she can do anything?

329
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:34,720
She doesn't know who she's dealing with.

330
00:24:37,120 --> 00:24:38,440
What are you going to do?

331
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:42,480
Picking a fight with them
will inevitably harm your business.

332
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,080
I don't care if my business goes bankrupt.

333
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:49,000
Let it be known that no one
talks trash about my wife.

334
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:55,560
I think it's best if you go back
and talk things through.

335
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:58,600
Don't throw your marriage away over this.

336
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:02,800
You're way younger than me.

337
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:04,680
Don't you dare lecture me.

338
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:26,360
Uncle Ree.

339
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:28,880
Hmm?

340
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:31,720
Do you think

341
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:33,880
Mr. Poj and Ms. Srichan

342
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:36,240
will ever reconcile?

343
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:39,400
Hmm.

344
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:41,840
What if they actually
end up getting a divorce?

345
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:44,280
What are we going to do?

346
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:49,480
Uncle Ree.

347
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:54,680
Are you looking for trouble?

348
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:57,400
Fine, then. I'm ready for it.

349
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:05,360
Have you ever heard this?

350
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:09,000
"No mistake is too great
for love to forgive."

351
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:12,840
Of course I have…

352
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:15,040
It's by Kahlil Gibran.

353
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:21,400
Did you gain this insight while serving
rich families in the past too?

354
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:32,200
But what if the love is really gone?

355
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,800
What's the solution to that?

356
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:05,360
Go get some sleep.
We need to head out early tomorrow.

357
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:07,360
Where are you going?

358
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:12,800
Since we're getting a divorce,
I should be sleeping in the other room.

359
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:14,840
Who said I'm going to divorce?

360
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:25,800
Hey.

361
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:28,800
Promise me.

362
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,560
About what?

363
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:32,600
First.

364
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:35,760
Stop being a workaholic and abandoning me.

365
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,680
You have enough wealth for ten lifetimes.

366
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,680
What are you hoarding all that money for?

367
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:43,240
If you love money so much,
why bother getting a wife?

368
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:46,960
How about I only work five days a week,

369
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:49,480
keep my weekends free,
and never bring my work home?

370
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:50,640
Deal?

371
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:53,560
Deal.

372
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,200
Easy.

373
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:57,640
Second.

374
00:27:57,720 --> 00:28:00,360
You must take me out on dates

375
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:02,560
and dinner every few days.

376
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:03,640
-Sure.
-When the war ends,

377
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:06,440
we're traveling abroad
and visiting the countryside.

378
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:09,320
I've been stuck at home so much
that I'm turning into a house ghost.

379
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:12,880
-Hey.
-Ouch.

380
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:13,800
Stop.

381
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:15,240
Do you want a new diamond set

382
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:17,880
every month too?
You can go pick them out yourself.

383
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:19,480
Huh?

384
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,960
And if you ever break your promise,

385
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,760
I'll bring a side piece into our home.

386
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:31,800
Not a chance. I will never break it.

387
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:45,360
I haven't kissed you in such a long time.

388
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:51,520
Ah, so refreshing.
You're so adorable. Give me a hug.

389
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:58,560
So, you two have reconciled?

390
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:01,440
Of course we did.

391
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:04,560
That's why I dropped by to thank you
before heading back to Bangkok.

392
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:06,360
No need to thank me.

393
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:07,920
I'm just relieved

394
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:10,320
you aren't blaming me
for that terrible advice I gave you.

395
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:15,560
Now that things are good between us,

396
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:17,320
let's forget the rest.

397
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:22,520
Anyway, Sri told me everything.

398
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:24,360
Rest assured,

399
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:26,960
I won't tell a soul who you really are.

400
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:29,760
Thank you so much.

401
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:35,040
But seriously, isn't it suffocating
living like this?

402
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:36,280
What do you mean?

403
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:37,520
Well,

404
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:40,240
about Miss Rajit.

405
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:43,120
Staying here as her older relative

406
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:44,800
completely ties your hands.

407
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:47,160
Why not just reveal the truth

408
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:50,520
and pursue her properly?

409
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:51,880
Right?

410
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:54,560
She's my friend's niece, Mr. Poj.

411
00:29:54,640 --> 00:29:56,520
I would never dare to think that.

412
00:29:57,880 --> 00:30:01,000
If you say so… Uncle Ree.

413
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:03,600
Please don't tease me.

414
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:07,960
You know well enough

415
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,200
that I'm completely broke.

416
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,800
Even my own fiancée
broke off our engagement.

417
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:18,480
How could I possibly dare
to dream of such things now?

418
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:29,680
Are you secretly seeing Tri?

419
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:35,600
Ms. Srichan. You're joking around
like this again.

420
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:38,320
We're uncle and niece.

421
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:40,760
Who would think that way?

422
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:45,600
What if he weren't your uncle? Would you?

423
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:52,520
Can't answer that?

424
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:56,840
Look, I won't tell a soul.

425
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,880
Besides, I'm returning to Bangkok.

426
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:01,760
I won't be standing in your way.

427
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,120
You're getting ahead of yourself.

428
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:07,480
Uncle Ree is my uncle.
How could he be anyone else?

429
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:10,600
You asked such a bizarre question.

430
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:13,280
So it took me a moment to respond.

431
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:26,560
A guy like you
isn't good enough for anyone,

432
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:28,480
Thatri.

433
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:49,960
-No, please. Spare us!
-We surrender!

434
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:51,240
Shut up!

435
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:53,080
Loot the place clean!

436
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:55,920
-Just take everything!
-Take it all!

437
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:57,160
I said, shut your mouth!

438
00:31:58,160 --> 00:32:00,360
Take it all. Just don't hurt us.

439
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,000
Just take everything.

440
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,480
Is this all you got?

441
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:40,000
This isn't even worth the pearls I spent.

442
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:42,800
That's just how it is during wartime.

443
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:45,080
Nobody is reckless enough
to buy luxuries anymore.

444
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:47,040
Then next time,

445
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:49,120
learn to target wealthier houses,

446
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:50,920
so there's actually a decent haul for us.

447
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,320
I get it.

448
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:54,840
If there's nothing else,
I'm taking my leave.

449
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:56,640
Wait.

450
00:32:57,680 --> 00:32:58,640
What is it?

451
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:03,960
Do you know who's been undercutting
our prices in the black market?

452
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:06,760
Not yet.

453
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:11,560
You can't get a single damn thing right!

454
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,840
But I did know that the Japanese

455
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:18,480
are moving a massive cargo
into Phuket soon.

456
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:37,360
Word is that Zhang Gong Cheng
has raided another local household.

457
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:41,120
I'm worried about the arrival
of the Japanese military in Phuket.

458
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:44,760
I share your concern.

459
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:46,680
If the military supplies

460
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:49,600
being transported this time are looted,

461
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,040
the Japanese

462
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:55,160
will suffer a massive setback
for a very long time.

463
00:33:57,960 --> 00:34:00,200
Can't you increase the security escort?

464
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:02,200
As of now, I doubt we can hold them off.

465
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:04,640
If I could do that,

466
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:08,280
I wouldn't have requested assistance
from the Thai authorities

467
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,000
in the first place.

468
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:13,280
Right now,

469
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:15,280
the war situation

470
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:16,920
is extremely critical.

471
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:20,199
I must keep my troops stationed

472
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:22,960
only at absolute vital positions.

473
00:34:28,719 --> 00:34:30,560
So, what's our move now?

474
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:23,720
Who the hell are you?
And why are you following me?

475
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:24,880
Speak up right now.

476
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:27,520
Mr. Thatri, it's me.

477
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:34,840
Wai? Is that you?

478
00:35:35,880 --> 00:35:38,320
-Yes, sir.
-Why were you sneaking around like that?

479
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:40,200
I could have broken your neck.

480
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:48,000
What are you looking at?

481
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:50,400
I'm afraid of being spotted.

482
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,880
I had to sneak around just to meet you.

483
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:55,680
To meet me? Why all the secrecy?

484
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,520
I don't get it.

485
00:35:58,120 --> 00:35:59,360
I came to warn you.

486
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:00,800
About what?

487
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:03,320
After leaving the Som Song Saeng house,

488
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:05,360
I've taken various jobs.

489
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:08,640
And now, I'm working for…

490
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:11,200
Get in here.

491
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:14,640
Am I really starting right away?

492
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:17,240
What about your boss? Won't he be angry?

493
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:19,200
He won't mind.

494
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:21,560
He ordered an urgent replacement
for the previous one.

495
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:24,400
Grab that and follow me.

496
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:33,080
All this gold… Where did they get it from?

497
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:38,000
Hurry up and load the goods.
We need to raid the next target.

498
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:39,080
Yes, Boss.

499
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:46,320
Raid?

500
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:52,360
What the hell are you doing?

501
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:56,800
Spying on the boss?

502
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:01,640
-The boss?
-Damn right.

503
00:37:02,240 --> 00:37:05,400
That's Zhang Gong Cheng, our boss.

504
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:07,040
They used to call him Black Beard,

505
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:09,800
but he got rid of the beard now.

506
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:12,520
Zhang Gong Cheng…

507
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:14,560
Stop standing there and help me lift this.

508
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:32,200
-We're almost done loading the goods.
-Good.

509
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:35,400
We can finally plan
to eliminate Thatri for good.

510
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:39,320
That damn Thatri.
I wish I could kill him right now.

511
00:37:45,040 --> 00:37:47,520
Hey, hurry up
and load the rest of the goods.

512
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:50,480
Yes, Boss. Hey, move your asses.

513
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:59,080
Thank you so much for warning me.

514
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:02,720
So, Zhang Gong Cheng's boss
is actually a woman?

515
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,160
Yes, sir.

516
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:06,120
But her voice sounded familiar to me.

517
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:12,040
Do you have any idea
why Zhang Gong Cheng leaves pearls

518
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:14,400
at the crime scenes after his raids?

519
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:16,520
I want to know his motive behind it.

520
00:38:16,600 --> 00:38:19,960
I don't know either.
Let me spy on them further.

521
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,720
Better not. I'm worried about your safety.

522
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:26,280
But I'm the only one
who can get this close to them, sir.

523
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:28,040
But it's too dangerous.

524
00:38:28,120 --> 00:38:31,840
Let me make amends for the awful things
I did to you and Miss Rajit, sir.

525
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:38,800
Just be careful then.

526
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:42,240
Zhang Gong Cheng and his men are ruthless.

527
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,920
If things go sideways, let me know.

528
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:45,720
I'll send backup right away.

529
00:38:45,800 --> 00:38:47,040
Yes, sir.

530
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:49,040
I'll take my leave now.

531
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:09,400
Uncle Ree.

532
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:12,920
Is there a blackout?

533
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:16,720
Yes. There's an issue with the generator.

534
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:20,560
Why aren't you using a flashlight?

535
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:23,400
Well, the batteries are completely dead.

536
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:25,640
Supplies haven't made it to Phuket yet.

537
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,040
Is the old man having a growth spurt?

538
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:43,360
If I grow more than this,
you might as well host my funeral.

539
00:39:45,160 --> 00:39:46,920
All the food has been put away.

540
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:49,840
Let me whip up
something quick for you to eat.

541
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:53,000
Go ahead. I actually miss
the taste of your food.

542
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:43,400
Here it is.

543
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:51,480
Are you eating this too?

544
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:54,920
Since I made it, I should enjoy it too.

545
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:58,680
The elderly might not want to grow,
but we youngsters still do.

546
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:04,920
So, this is the famous Phuket Mee Hoon
that I've heard so much about?

547
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:06,600
That's right.

548
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,560
But it's such a pity

549
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:10,920
we don't have
pork bone broth to go with it.

550
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:13,440
If paired together, it would taste better.

551
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:17,600
If it took any longer,
it would be breakfast time by then.

552
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:20,080
Having this dish is more than enough.

553
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:26,320
Give it a taste then, Uncle Ree,

554
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:27,680
and tell me if it's good.

555
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:43,240
This is delicious.

556
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:48,200
Just so you know,
this is Aunt Paetai's secret recipe.

557
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:51,120
Really?

558
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,920
Someone like her
could actually cook this well?

559
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:56,520
That's right.

560
00:41:56,600 --> 00:41:58,560
But ever since she got promoted

561
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:00,840
to assist Grandpa Som,

562
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,920
she hung up her apron

563
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:05,040
and became a loud, fussy madam

564
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:06,840
as you see today.

565
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:12,520
Back then, I used to enjoy
so many dishes made by her.

566
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:15,440
And you managed to learn her recipe.

567
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:19,320
Speaking of which,

568
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:21,840
I really miss how Aunt Paetai
used to be back then.

569
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:28,720
You must've been a child back then,

570
00:42:30,680 --> 00:42:33,040
considering how old your aunt is now.

571
00:42:44,760 --> 00:42:46,800
-Is it good?
-It's perfect.

572
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:02,080
I'm so happy for you.

573
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:04,680
At least you'll have someone to look after

574
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:06,640
and won't be left alone in your old age.

575
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:08,480
But I…

576
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:13,440
I feel absolutely terrible, Mother.

577
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:16,640
Today of all days

578
00:43:16,720 --> 00:43:19,680
is supposed to be
the happiest day of my life.

579
00:43:19,760 --> 00:43:21,520
Are you still yearning for that…

580
00:43:23,040 --> 00:43:24,960
that Thatri again?

581
00:43:28,080 --> 00:43:31,000
I don't miss Tri
in the way you think, Mother.

582
00:43:32,280 --> 00:43:34,400
If you ask me

583
00:43:35,560 --> 00:43:37,600
whether I ever truly loved him,

584
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:40,400
I honestly wouldn't even know
how to answer.

585
00:43:42,960 --> 00:43:44,880
To me,

586
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:48,480
marriage is merely a means of survival.

587
00:43:49,320 --> 00:43:50,760
Because in reality,

588
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:53,760
I love absolutely no one,

589
00:43:55,120 --> 00:43:56,840
neither Tri

590
00:43:57,920 --> 00:44:00,040
nor this groom of mine.

591
00:44:02,680 --> 00:44:05,000
Stop overthinking this, Sasi.

592
00:44:06,840 --> 00:44:08,600
Go pack your things.

593
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:11,880
It's time for you
to move in with your husband.

594
00:44:14,280 --> 00:44:17,440
Am I a horrible person, Mother?

595
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:23,240
Let the blame be mine.

596
00:44:23,320 --> 00:44:25,880
May all the bad karma
strike me down instead.

597
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:29,560
I am the one who forced you
into this marriage.

598
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:32,440
But I need you to know.

599
00:44:33,680 --> 00:44:36,360
Everything I've done
is entirely for our own good.

600
00:44:58,800 --> 00:44:59,640
What the hell?

601
00:45:00,640 --> 00:45:02,160
Your friend here is an ungrateful dog.

602
00:45:03,360 --> 00:45:04,880
He dared to steal from me.

603
00:45:06,520 --> 00:45:09,120
I didn't steal it, Boss.
Please, have mercy on me.

604
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:12,680
Caught red-handed with proof,
and you still dare to lie to me?

605
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:15,160
I saw it lying on the ground.
I was about to put it back,

606
00:45:15,240 --> 00:45:16,360
but you spotted me first, Boss.

607
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:17,800
I'm no thief.

608
00:45:18,440 --> 00:45:20,360
Wai. Help me.

609
00:45:20,440 --> 00:45:21,800
Don't you move.

610
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:23,680
Don't even think about it.

611
00:45:24,640 --> 00:45:27,040
Anyone who dares to steal my things,

612
00:45:27,640 --> 00:45:28,920
their penalty is death.

613
00:45:36,560 --> 00:45:37,520
Wai,

614
00:45:38,800 --> 00:45:40,600
if you are truly loyal to me,

615
00:45:42,080 --> 00:45:43,160
you must execute him.

616
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:47,200
Wai. No. Don't touch that gun.

617
00:45:47,280 --> 00:45:48,280
Wai.

618
00:45:49,960 --> 00:45:52,040
-You want me to shoot my own friend?
-Damn right.

619
00:45:54,720 --> 00:45:56,320
If you are my man,

620
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:58,280
you obey whatever orders I give you.

621
00:45:58,360 --> 00:45:59,560
Wai, please don't do this.

622
00:45:59,640 --> 00:46:03,040
Wai. Please don't.

623
00:46:03,120 --> 00:46:05,080
Please, I beg you. Don't kill me.

624
00:46:08,240 --> 00:46:11,160
Wai, please. Don't pick up the gun!

625
00:46:19,080 --> 00:46:20,440
Wai!

626
00:46:31,160 --> 00:46:32,920
Please forgive me, man.

627
00:46:36,680 --> 00:46:37,880
Wai!

628
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:50,840
You really can be trusted, after all.

629
00:46:56,040 --> 00:46:57,840
Welcome to the crew, Wai.

630
00:46:59,120 --> 00:47:00,040
Hey, let's celebrate!

631
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:03,560
Were you going to blow my brains out?

632
00:47:03,640 --> 00:47:06,000
-Damn, you've got real balls.
-Come on, boys.

633
00:47:06,080 --> 00:47:08,160
-Come on.
-Here.

634
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:09,920
Come on.

635
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:11,520
Let's cheer.

636
00:47:14,520 --> 00:47:16,560
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

637
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:30,120
Wai, keep watch and be our lookout.

638
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:31,080
Yes, Boss.

639
00:47:39,160 --> 00:47:42,720
Help! We're being robbed!

640
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:50,480
-Is everything cleared out?
-Yes, Boss.

641
00:48:25,600 --> 00:48:27,880
How did it go out there, Wai?

642
00:48:28,480 --> 00:48:31,400
Too easy, man.
Just broke a little sweat with the boss.

643
00:48:31,480 --> 00:48:32,840
Total walk in the park.

644
00:48:33,400 --> 00:48:35,480
Stop blowing your own horn, will you?

645
00:48:41,960 --> 00:48:44,280
Hey, actually, there's one thing
I'm curious about.

646
00:48:44,360 --> 00:48:45,680
What is it, Wai?

647
00:48:45,760 --> 00:48:49,320
How come the Boss always drops a pearl
right next to the dead bodies?

648
00:48:49,840 --> 00:48:51,320
The pearls?

649
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:54,120
I heard the pirate crew mentioning

650
00:48:54,200 --> 00:48:56,920
that the Boss Lady
ordered him to leave them there.

651
00:48:57,000 --> 00:49:00,000
It's an offering for the souls.
So their spirits won't seek vengeance.

652
00:49:00,600 --> 00:49:02,280
They're top-grade pearls, too.

653
00:49:02,360 --> 00:49:05,080
Cost a fortune, really.

654
00:49:05,160 --> 00:49:07,160
Though if you ask me,

655
00:49:07,240 --> 00:49:08,720
those dead bastards

656
00:49:08,800 --> 00:49:10,680
probably have no use for them anyway.

657
00:49:12,160 --> 00:49:13,480
-You want one then?
-Hell no.

658
00:49:13,560 --> 00:49:15,560
Are you out of your mind?
That means I'm dead.

659
00:49:17,960 --> 00:49:20,320
Does Zhang Gong Cheng's boss
actually hold such a belief?

660
00:49:20,400 --> 00:49:23,640
I'm not quite sure, sir,
but that's what they told me.

661
00:49:25,200 --> 00:49:28,440
If they can afford pearls,
they must be wealthy.

662
00:49:29,640 --> 00:49:30,600
Exactly, sir.

663
00:49:30,680 --> 00:49:32,800
The reason he can walk around
so high and mighty

664
00:49:32,880 --> 00:49:36,120
is probably because
there's an influential figure backing him.

665
00:49:39,960 --> 00:49:42,080
That aligns with what
the District Officer once said.

666
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:45,600
Wai, here's the plan.

667
00:50:18,720 --> 00:50:21,600
Where did you sneak off to?
Did you think I wouldn't find out?

668
00:50:21,680 --> 00:50:23,200
You went to see Thatri.

669
00:50:23,960 --> 00:50:24,960
That's right, Boss.

670
00:50:27,160 --> 00:50:28,760
I was planning

671
00:50:29,400 --> 00:50:31,200
to lure him straight into a trap.

672
00:50:32,680 --> 00:50:34,080
Why would you do that?

673
00:50:34,160 --> 00:50:35,480
Because I despise him.

674
00:50:36,000 --> 00:50:37,680
You probably didn't know this,

675
00:50:37,760 --> 00:50:40,240
but I used to work at their house.

676
00:50:45,160 --> 00:50:46,320
Is that so?

677
00:50:48,160 --> 00:50:49,400
Yes, Boss.

678
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:52,200
I was kicked out because of him.

679
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:54,880
So when I found out
that you were planning to kill him,

680
00:50:55,520 --> 00:50:56,600
I wanted to lend a hand.

681
00:50:57,640 --> 00:50:58,760
So what?

682
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:01,040
If you hate his guts,

683
00:51:01,800 --> 00:51:03,920
why didn't you just do it
and be done with it?

684
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:07,760
Do you honestly think
I wouldn't have killed him

685
00:51:07,840 --> 00:51:11,400
if I had the chance?
But the fool accidentally leaked intel

686
00:51:11,480 --> 00:51:13,080
regarding a Japanese supply shipment.

687
00:51:14,120 --> 00:51:16,320
I knew you've been itching to raid them,

688
00:51:16,400 --> 00:51:19,720
so I kept him alive
just to get his information.

689
00:51:21,600 --> 00:51:22,760
What information?

690
00:51:25,400 --> 00:51:27,000
Here is our transport data,

691
00:51:27,080 --> 00:51:29,960
including the cargo details,
the departure times,

692
00:51:30,560 --> 00:51:31,920
and the exact supply routes.

693
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:33,800
I've already leaked all of it to Wai.

694
00:51:35,480 --> 00:51:38,760
Do you truly place
this much trust in that man?

695
00:51:40,080 --> 00:51:40,920
Yes, I do.

696
00:51:42,480 --> 00:51:45,520
If you trust him, Thatri-san,
then so do I.

697
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:50,240
As for my men,
the forces are fully deployed.

698
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:53,240
We await your direct command,
Colonel Nakamura.

699
00:52:01,520 --> 00:52:03,400
He trusts me completely.

700
00:52:04,160 --> 00:52:05,880
He'd never suspect that I'd turn on him.

701
00:52:05,960 --> 00:52:08,040
Now, all you have to do
is double-cross him,

702
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:09,920
slit his throat,

703
00:52:10,680 --> 00:52:12,800
and seize all the supply shipments.

704
00:52:13,840 --> 00:52:15,920
You aren't trying
to play me for a fool, are you?

705
00:52:17,920 --> 00:52:20,960
Boss, if it weren't for Thatri,

706
00:52:21,040 --> 00:52:23,440
I wouldn't be living like this.

707
00:52:24,520 --> 00:52:25,760
How so?

708
00:52:25,840 --> 00:52:28,240
My mother was Som's mistress,

709
00:52:28,320 --> 00:52:30,600
yet we didn't inherit a single thing.

710
00:52:30,680 --> 00:52:32,520
Meanwhile, Thatri,

711
00:52:33,040 --> 00:52:35,280
who hadn't even seen the old man's face,

712
00:52:35,880 --> 00:52:37,360
walked away with half the fortune.

713
00:52:37,440 --> 00:52:39,200
How am I supposed to not hate him?

714
00:52:40,920 --> 00:52:44,320
Not to mention how he kicked me out,
discarding me like a worthless dog.

715
00:52:53,960 --> 00:52:56,600
ADISUAN PEARLS

716
00:52:56,680 --> 00:52:59,640
Do you think we can trust
someone like Wai?

717
00:53:00,280 --> 00:53:02,760
I'm not so sure how trustworthy he is,

718
00:53:02,840 --> 00:53:06,320
but every single thing
Wai told you is the absolute truth.

719
00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:10,560
Both the part where Thatri kicked him out
for trying to kill Rajit

720
00:53:11,240 --> 00:53:13,600
and the fact that his mother
was Uncle Som's mistress.

721
00:53:22,200 --> 00:53:23,760
But just to be safe,

722
00:53:24,280 --> 00:53:27,600
make sure you prepare a backup plan
before launching the raid.

723
00:53:28,280 --> 00:53:31,200
It has to be a plan
that Thatri would never see coming.

724
00:53:31,280 --> 00:53:33,800
And Wai must be kept
completely in the dark.

725
00:53:34,320 --> 00:53:35,720
Brilliant.

726
00:53:50,360 --> 00:53:51,720
What's all this?

727
00:53:53,080 --> 00:53:55,400
Just some things
we might need during the raid.

728
00:53:57,040 --> 00:53:58,360
What is it even for?

729
00:53:59,320 --> 00:54:01,000
Stop asking so many damn questions.

730
00:54:02,840 --> 00:54:04,080
Just be our lookout here.

731
00:54:05,320 --> 00:54:07,440
If the police or the Japanese
show up around here,

732
00:54:07,960 --> 00:54:10,200
fire this signal flare to warn us.

733
00:54:11,560 --> 00:54:14,120
You're leaving me behind.
Do you not trust me?

734
00:54:14,200 --> 00:54:16,080
Why are you being so paranoid?

735
00:54:16,720 --> 00:54:19,160
You've always been
our lookout from day one.

736
00:54:20,600 --> 00:54:21,520
Yes, Boss.

737
00:54:25,280 --> 00:54:26,120
Move out.

738
00:54:26,720 --> 00:54:27,760
Yes, Boss.

739
00:54:36,600 --> 00:54:37,480
-Hey.
-Hey.

740
00:54:54,240 --> 00:54:56,600
There really aren't
any Japanese soldiers around.

741
00:55:03,680 --> 00:55:05,480
Wai really is trustworthy after all.

742
00:55:06,840 --> 00:55:09,840
Go grab that truck
and seize their supplies.

743
00:55:10,600 --> 00:55:12,720
-Their reinforcements will be here soon.
-Yes, Boss.

744
00:55:12,800 --> 00:55:14,080
Move.

745
00:55:19,600 --> 00:55:22,200
Zhang Gong Cheng's crew
really did show up to raid us.

746
00:55:25,520 --> 00:55:26,800
Everyone, get ready.

747
00:55:27,760 --> 00:55:29,320
Please be careful, Mr. Thatri.

748
00:55:29,400 --> 00:55:31,720
If you get hurt, the Chief will kill me.

749
00:55:31,800 --> 00:55:32,920
Don't worry.

750
00:55:34,560 --> 00:55:35,720
Attack!

751
00:55:35,800 --> 00:55:36,960
-Go!
-Go!

752
00:55:43,520 --> 00:55:44,960
Freeze! Don't move!

753
00:55:51,480 --> 00:55:53,040
You're slower than I expected.

754
00:55:53,120 --> 00:55:55,080
What's the meaning of this?

755
00:55:56,320 --> 00:55:58,840
It means I've prepared
a little welcoming gift for you.

756
00:55:59,440 --> 00:56:01,360
I don't care about your petty tricks.

757
00:56:01,880 --> 00:56:04,920
If you fear the police's bullets,
you'd better surrender right now.

758
00:56:06,600 --> 00:56:08,000
-Hey!
-Hey!

759
00:56:15,160 --> 00:56:16,800
Did you forget we're in the jungle?

760
00:56:16,880 --> 00:56:18,840
We have guns too, you fool!

761
00:56:34,880 --> 00:56:37,200
What did you go to Bangkok for,
District Chief?

762
00:56:37,280 --> 00:56:38,400
I went there to get married.

763
00:56:38,480 --> 00:56:39,520
-Married?
-Married?

764
00:56:39,600 --> 00:56:40,560
Here she is.

765
00:56:43,040 --> 00:56:45,280
-Tri?
-Sasi?

766
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:47,720
You must take them down today.

767
00:56:47,800 --> 00:56:50,440
I've noted every single detail,
including the escape routes.

768
00:56:50,520 --> 00:56:52,080
Freeze! Don't move!

769
00:56:52,160 --> 00:56:53,040
Drop your weapons!

770
00:56:57,240 --> 00:56:58,200
Die, you bastard.

771
00:57:03,200 --> 00:57:05,000
So, they used to be engaged.

772
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:07,800
Old flames won't reignite,
will they, Rajit?

773
00:57:07,880 --> 00:57:09,880
A one-winged bird can't fly alone,

774
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:12,120
so I guess it's grounded forever.

775
00:57:40,920 --> 00:57:43,080
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
